anstelle dessen einen synthetischen Ansatz verfolgt, der muslimische Wissensbestände theoriegenerierend mit aufnimmt.  aReferences to "Islamic tradition" are omnipresent in the general public sphere and in scholarship. However, there has not been much consideration of what actually constitutes Islamic tradition. This volume attempts to ground Islamic tradition in the theory of tradition in order to subsequently ask how this understanding can open up perspectives for an Islamic discourse theology.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aGesellschaft. 4aIslam. 4aModerne. 4aRelligion.  aIslam.  amodernity.  areligion.  asociety.2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831107947310 cprintz978311079455740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110794656zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110794656zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110794656/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA